From: Prajw <prajw@trivartatech>
Date: Sun, 26 Apr 2026 19:16:26 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?fix:=20bulk=20reset=20failed=20=E2=80=94=20user?=
 =?UTF-8?q?=5Ftype=20is=20a=20backed=20enum,=20not=20a=20string?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

PHP 8 throws an Error when you cast a backed enum to string directly:
(string) UserType::Parent → Error: Object of class UserType could not
be converted to string.

bulkReset() was hitting that on every user. Now uses ->value when the
attribute is a BackedEnum, falls back to string cast otherwise. Also
formats roles like 'super_admin' → 'Super admin' for display in the
exported credentials table.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 app/Http/Controllers/School/UserManagementController.php | 7 ++++++-
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/app/Http/Controllers/School/UserManagementController.php b/app/Http/Controllers/School/UserManagementController.php
index e17d724..093856d 100644
--- a/app/Http/Controllers/School/UserManagementController.php
+++ b/app/Http/Controllers/School/UserManagementController.php
@@ -276,9 +276,14 @@ public function bulkReset(Request $request)
             foreach ($users as $u) {
                 $newPassword = Str::random(10);
                 $u->update(['password' => Hash::make($newPassword)]);
+                // user_type is a backed enum (App\Enums\UserType), so we must
+                // pull ->value rather than relying on string cast.
+                $role = $u->user_type instanceof \BackedEnum
+                    ? $u->user_type->value
+                    : (string) ($u->user_type ?? '');
                 $rows[] = [
                     'name'     => $u->name,
-                    'role'     => ucfirst((string) $u->user_type),
+                    'role'     => ucfirst(str_replace('_', ' ', $role)),
                     'username' => $u->username,
                     'password' => $newPassword,
                 ];
